SIMPLE: subinfeudation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subinfeudation
<hw>Sub*in`feu*da"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The granting of lands by inferior lords to their
dependents, to be held by themselves by feudal tenure.</def>
<au>Craig.</au> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Subordinate tenancy;
undertenancy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The widow is immediate tenant to the heir, by a kind of
<qex>subinfeudation</qex>, or undertenancy.</q>
<rj><qau>Blackstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subingression</ent>⟦br⟧
